title: Appointment to Lotteries Fund Advisory Committee announced
content_text: The Government today (August 31) announced the appointment of seven members to the Lotteries Fund Advisory Committee (LFAC) for a period of two years, with effect from September 1, 2001. The LFAC was renamed from the Subventions and Lotteries Fund Advisory Committee (SLFAC) in view of its refocussed role to advise the Director of Social Welfare on applications from welfare agencies for allocations from the Lotteries Fund and for permission to hold flag days.
